<title>USA: Illinois sues tobacco companies, seeks health care costs.</title>
<headline>Illinois sues tobacco companies, seeks health care costs.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1996-11-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Illinois Attorney General Jim Ryan filed an 11-count lawsuit against the tobacco industry on Tuesday, making it the sixteenth state seeking to recover hundreds of millions of dollars in smoking related health care costs.</p>
<p>The suit alleges that the tobacco companies deceived Illinois consumers, targeted minors and unfairly forced state taxpayers to incur costs related to the health care of its citizens, a statement by the Illinois Attorney General's office said.</p>
